been updated since this variable was introduced and is unlikely to
be updated any time soon.

mentions `vterm-mode-hook', but the documentation
referred to `vterm-exec-hook'.

commit.message:
with-editor--setup: Replace leading "~" with home directory

Otherwise it would get quoted, resulting in an invalid path.
Even if that weren't the case, we still would have to expand
"~", because git doesn't know what that means.

with-editor--setup: Shell-quote executable again

Quoting is the right thing to do.  Applications that fail because of
that, are the ones that need fixing, in the case of shell script, by
using:

  eval "$EDITOR" file

Fixes #121.
